summary:
I need to say something uncomfortable.
At first, when Taylor announced the stadium tour I was a bit doubtful about her team’s...
body:
I need to say something uncomfortable.

At first, when Taylor announced the stadium tour I was a bit doubtful about her team’s decision of playing in those massive stadiums. Looking at the quantity of tickets that were still available so close to the concert dates, I thought she wouldn’t sold out any of the dates. I was also very upset for the way they organized tickets with this new slow selling method, because in the presale i couldn’t choose where I wanted to be and I still find it crazy…

Anyway, I need to say I was completely wrong! As always Taylor is doing great and I’m really happy she managed to deal with such big events, looking at those stadiums full of people is a magical experience. She’s so talented and she always knows what she’s doing.

I should never have doubted that. 💕

Anna🌹 | very much in love with Taylor Swift & photography |
Taylor held my hand on 06/09/18 in Manchester |

summary: The picture above took my sisters boyfriend at a festival two weeks ago. My  sister Maria (right) has been my best friend for...
body:
touuuur post ✨

hey✨

The picture above took my sisters boyfriend at a festival two weeks ago. My sister Maria (right) has been my best friend for over 15 years now and I couldn’t be happier with her.

Quick story:

When my sister was in high school, her best friend bought her “Fearless” as a birthday present. I was about 7 at that time. She listened to it every day and back than, we shared a room - so I also listened to it every day. Neither I knew Taylor nor I could really understand what kind of talent she had back than.

The songs of Fearless has been there when I cried in my sisters arms the night before Christmas because of the loss my father had to experiment years ago. Her songs were there when we laughed till we cried and even when we started to fight.

As I said, I didn’t know Taylor than. The moment I noticed it was Taylor …was about two and a half, almost three years ago, when I started listening to her music and loving her. When I first really listened to Fearless, I had to notice that I already knew the words to the songs. Because I grew up with them.

In 2012, my sister played “Everything Has Changed” for me. And, I still can’t believe it, I said to her: Who is this girl who tries to sing louder than the boy?

And my sister was angry at me, I remember it well.

Then, in 2015, Maria bought me 1989 for Christmas and I remember screaming and crying and listening to it without understanding a word … That day changed my life and my English grade because since then, I really started listening to Taylor and her stories which improved my English btw so much, it’s unbelievable.

Taylor has been there when I got my heart broken for the first time which was an awful but yet needed experience I had to make.

Becoming a Swiftie will forever be the one thing I did right.

I became a Swiftie because of my sister and I will forever be thankful.

This attitude got stronger as my sister bought us tickets for Manchester Night 2 (june 9th). I’m still in denial and I’m not quite sure if that will change till I see my best friend on stage. The thing is, we never had much money and since we’re living in Germany, Manchester was not reachable…at least was that my first thought.

I’ve never been happier about a present. Even if my time as a Swiftie is short compared to the whole 11 year thing, I love Taylor from the bottom of my heart. She was there when no one was and hugged me with her songs.

We’ll sit in Section B2, Row F, Seats 5 and 6.

The first time I’ll ever be to a concert and I’m so excited! It’s gonna be a crazy night!

With love,

Anna

trail.content:
touuuur post ✨

hey✨

The picture above took my sisters boyfriend at a festival two weeks ago. My sister Maria (right) has been my best friend for over 15 years now and I couldn’t be happier with her.

Quick story:

When my sister was in high school, her best friend bought her “Fearless” as a birthday present. I was about 7 at that time. She listened to it every day and back than, we shared a room - so I also listened to it every day. Neither I knew Taylor nor I could really understand what kind of talent she had back than.

The songs of Fearless has been there when I cried in my sisters arms the night before Christmas because of the loss my father had to experiment years ago. Her songs were there when we laughed till we cried and even when we started to fight.

As I said, I didn’t know Taylor than. The moment I noticed it was Taylor …was about two and a half, almost three years ago, when I started listening to her music and loving her. When I first really listened to Fearless, I had to notice that I already knew the words to the songs. Because I grew up with them.

In 2012, my sister played “Everything Has Changed” for me. And, I still can’t believe it, I said to her: Who is this girl who tries to sing louder than the boy?

And my sister was angry at me, I remember it well.

Then, in 2015, Maria bought me 1989 for Christmas and I remember screaming and crying and listening to it without understanding a word … That day changed my life and my English grade because since then, I really started listening to Taylor and her stories which improved my English btw so much, it’s unbelievable.

Taylor has been there when I got my heart broken for the first time which was an awful but yet needed experience I had to make.

Becoming a Swiftie will forever be the one thing I did right.

I became a Swiftie because of my sister and I will forever be thankful.

This attitude got stronger as my sister bought us tickets for Manchester Night 2 (june 9th). I’m still in denial and I’m not quite sure if that will change till I see my best friend on stage. The thing is, we never had much money and since we’re living in Germany, Manchester was not reachable…at least was that my first thought.

I’ve never been happier about a present. Even if my time as a Swiftie is short compared to the whole 11 year thing, I love Taylor from the bottom of my heart. She was there when no one was and hugged me with her songs.

We’ll sit in Section B2, Row F, Seats 5 and 6.

The first time I’ll ever be to a concert and I’m so excited! It’s gonna be a crazy night!

With love,

Anna
